Hierarchical clustering

Problem Statement:-

  • Perform clustering (Both hierarchical and K means clustering) for the airlines data to obtain optimum number of clusters. Draw the inferences from the clusters obtained.

Scaling

Before applying Hierarchical Clustering, we have to normalize the data so that the scale of each variable is the same. Why is this important? Well, if the scale of the variables is not the same, the model might become biased towards the variables with a higher magnitude.

airlines_scaled <- as.data.frame(scale(airlines))
summary(airlines_scaled)

Since all the values here are continuous numerical values, you will use the euclidean distance method.

Building the Model

dist_mat <- dist(airlines_scaled, method = 'euclidean')
hclust_ward <- hclust(dist_mat, method = 'ward.D2')
#Plotting the dendrogram
plot(hclust_ward)

The x-axis contains the samples and y-axis represents the distance between these samples. The vertical line with maximum distance is the blue line and hence we can decide a threshold of 80 and cut the dendrogram:We will get 5 clusters after cutting the dendrogram at hight 80.

Cutting the Dendrogram

cut_ward <- cutree(hclust_ward, k = 5)
plot(hclust_ward)
rect.hclust(hclust_ward , k = 5, border = 2:6)
abline(h = 80, col = 'red')

Let’s visualize the tree with different colored branches using package dendextend

suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(dendextend))
ward_dend_obj <- as.dendrogram(hclust_ward)
ward_col_dend <- color_branches(ward_dend_obj, h = 80)
plot(ward_col_dend)

#Appending the clusters to original dataframe.
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(dplyr))
airlines_cl <- mutate(airlines, cluster = cut_ward)
head(airlines_cl)

Visualizing few attributes

suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(ggplot2))
ggplot(airlines_cl, aes(x=Balance, y = Qual_miles, color = factor(cluster))) + geom_point()

suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(ggplot2))
ggplot(airlines_cl, aes(x=Bonus_trans, y = Bonus_miles, color = factor(cluster))) + geom_point()

#Writing the final file with assigned cluster IDs.
write.csv(airlines_cl, file="~/desktop/Digi 360/Module 12/airlines_final_R.csv")

Conclusion

  • Chosen the threshold as 80 to cut the dendrogram considering above this threshold is maximum distance.
  • The cut-off line is intersecting at five points in dendrogram, so 5 clusters have been chosen.
